    "pathname": "ario",
    "name": "Achaemenid Royal Inscriptions online",
    "abbrev": "ARIo",
    "project-type": "corpus",
    "blurb": "The project presents annotated and searchable editions of Achaemenid Royal Inscriptions written in Old Persian, Elamite, and Akkadian. The open-access editions are based on Rüdiger Schmitt's Die altpersischen Inschriften der Achaimeniden (2009) and data provided by Dr. Matt Stolper (from his now-defunct Achaemenid Royal Inscriptions project). The texts have been adapted, lemmatized, and translated into English by <a href=\" https://www.en.ag.geschichte.uni-muenchen.de/staff/staff/heitmann-gordon/index.html\">Henry Heitmann-Gordon</a>. The project is a sub-project of the Munich Open-access Cuneiform Corpus Initiative (MOCCI), which is funded by LMU Munich and the <a href=\"https://www.humboldt-foundation.de/web/home.html\">Alexander von Humboldt Foundation</a>.",
